																																												</figure>
																																											</div>
																																											<div class="emm-container__grid">
																																												<h2>3. Prepare your body for sleep</h2>
																																												<p>Our physical health and how we look after our body can have a big effect on our sleep. It can be easy to fall into unhealthy patterns of behaviour that can make your sleep worse, especially at times like these.</p>
																																												<p>Having caffeine, alcohol, nicotine or a big meal too close to bedtime can stop you falling asleep and prevent deep sleep. Try to avoid them before bed and see if things improve.</p>
																																												<p>Regular exercise is also great for sleep. Just remember to steer clear of anything too vigorous right before bedtime if you find it affects your sleep, and make sure you follow the social distancing guidelines when exercising.</p>
																																											</div>
																																										</div>
																																									</div>
																																								</div>
																																							</div>
																																						</section>
																																						<section class="nhsuk-section app-section "  id="4" >
																																							<div class="nhsuk-width-container">
																																								<div class="nhsuk-grid-row">
																																									<div class="nhsuk-grid-column-full nhsuk-section__content">
																																										<div class="nhsuk-u-reading-width"></div>
																																										<div class="emm-container emm-align-right">
